@section Meta

This specification was written after the fact, reconstructing decisions from code and usage. Future decisions should be documented as they're made, using the memory layer's decision trail feature.

The self-referential nature is intentional: form-copilot helps complete complex multi-section documents; this specification is a complex multi-section document about form-copilot.



@node RFC 001
@chapter RFC 001: Beads, Quint, and Synthesis Integration


@noindent
@strong{Status:} Implemented (v0.3.0)

@noindent
@strong{Author:} Aaron Johnson

@noindent
@strong{Created:} 2026-02-05

@noindent
@strong{Implemented:} 2026-02-05

@noindent
@strong{Branch:} @code{rfc/beads-quint-synthesis}



@section Decisions (resolved during implementation)

@enumerate
@item
@strong{Beads/quint as inspiration, not dependency.} RFC 002 implemented
   the patterns in pure Python rather than depending on beads CLI or
   quint MCP server. Same concepts (task graphs, decision trails,
   synthesis), zero external dependencies.
@end enumerate

@enumerate
@item
@strong{SQLite kept as regenerable index}, not removed. JSONL is the
   source of truth; SQLite provides fast queries. This is better than
   either "SQLite only" (not git-friendly) or "JSONL only" (slow queries).
@end enumerate

@enumerate
@item
@strong{Sections as labels, not beads.} Questions use labels
   (@code{section:business_overview}) rather than a parent task hierarchy.
   Simpler, works well enough.
@end enumerate

@enumerate
@item
@strong{Synthesis runs in-process}, not via Claude API calls. Pattern
   detection and coherence checks use Python logic over the task/decision
   data, not LLM prompts. LLM-powered synthesis can be added later.
@end enumerate



@section Summary

Replace form-copilot's direct SQLite storage with a layered memory architecture using @uref{https://github.com/steveyegge/beads, beads} for task/answer tracking, @uref{https://github.com/m0n0x41d/quint-code, quint-code} for decision reasoning trails, and a new synthesis layer that extracts insights across accumulated context.


@section Motivation

Current form-copilot stores answers in SQLite and events in @code{session_log.json}. This works but misses opportunities:

@enumerate
@item
@strong{No dependency graph} - Questions have @code{depends_on} in config but answers don't track relationships
@item
@strong{No reasoning trails} - We know @emph{what} was answered but not @emph{why} that framing was chosen
@item
@strong{No synthesis} - Completed answers accumulate but don't connect into insights
@item
@strong{Session-bound context} - Each Claude session starts fresh; learnings don't compound
@end enumerate


@section Design Principles

@itemize @bullet
@item
@strong{Integrate, don't reimplement} - beads and quint are mature tools; use them
@item
@strong{Synthesis over summarization} - Compression should surface patterns, not just shorten text
@item
@strong{Git-native} - All state survives in version control
@item
@strong{Agent-friendly} - Structure enables Claude to reason across sessions
@end itemize


@section Architecture


@example
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   form-copilot                       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Interface Layer (existing)                         │
│  - sea_assistant.py menu system                     │
│  - .claude/commands/ for Claude Code                │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Synthesis Layer (new)                              │
│  - Pattern detection across completed work          │
│  - Cross-reference discovery                        │
│  - Context decay with insight preservation          │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Storage Layer (refactored)                         │
│  - beads (.beads/) - questions, answers, deps       │
│  - quint (.quint/) - decision reasoning trails      │
│  - SQLite removed as primary store                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
@end example


@section Beads Integration


@subsection Mapping


@multitable @columnfractions 0.50 0.50
@headitem Current (SQLite) @tab Beads Equivalent
@item @code{questions} table @tab Config-driven (unchanged)
@item @code{answers} table @tab @code{bd create} with answer as description
@item @code{answers.status} @tab Bead status (open/in_progress/closed)
@item @code{answers.notes} @tab Bead comments
@item @code{depends_on} @tab @code{bd block} relationships
@item Progress queries @tab @code{bd ready}, @code{bd list --status}
@end multitable



@subsection Task Hierarchy


@example
Form (epic)
└── Section (task)
    └── Question (subtask)
        └── Answer iterations (comments/history)
@end example


@subsection Example Flow


@example
# Initialize form as beads project
bd init

# Create section
bd create "Section: Business Overview" --label section

# Create question under section
bd create "What problem does your business solve?" \
  --parent bd-a1b2 \
  --label question \
  --label priority:1

# Save answer
bd comment bd-a1b2.1 "Answer: We reduce complexity in..."
bd close bd-a1b2.1
@end example


@section Quint Integration


@subsection Decision Points

Not every answer needs a decision trail. Track reasoning when:
@itemize @bullet
@item
Choosing between multiple valid framings
@item
Making trade-offs (brevity vs completeness)
@item
Connecting answer to external context (resume, other applications)
@end itemize


@subsection Example


@example
# Before finalizing an answer
/q1-hypothesize
# H1: Lead with technical depth
# H2: Lead with business impact
# H3: Lead with personal narrative

/q2-verify
# Checking against: role requirements, company culture, section context

/q5-decide
# Selected H2: Business impact framing matches startup audience
@end example


@subsection Storage

Decisions persist in @code{.quint/} directory, queryable later:
@itemize @bullet
@item
"Why did I frame the leadership answer around delegation?"
@item
"What trade-offs did I consider for the technical question?"
@end itemize


@section Synthesis Layer


@subsection Purpose

Transform accumulated answers and decisions into actionable insights.


@subsection Operations

@strong{1. Pattern Detection}

@example
synthesize patterns

Output:
- Theme "systems thinking" appears in 4/7 answers
- Gap: No answers reference quantitative achievements
- Consistency: All technical answers mention integration work
@end example

@strong{2. Cross-Reference Discovery}

@example
synthesize connections --question bd-a3f8

Output:
- Answer bd-a3f8 (leadership) aligns with decision qt-002
- Related closed bead bd-a2c1 covers same ground differently
- Consider consolidating framing
@end example

@strong{3. Context Decay}

@example
synthesize decay --older-than 30d

Output:
- Compressing 12 closed beads from January
- Preserved insights:
  - "Integration expertise" is core positioning
  - Passed on roles requiring deep ML specialization
- Raw answers archived, summaries active
@end example


@subsection Implementation

Synthesis runs Claude against beads/quint data:
@enumerate
@item
Load relevant beads (by label, status, date)
@item
Load related quint decisions
@item
Prompt Claude for pattern/connection/decay analysis
@item
Store synthesis as new bead with @code{--label synthesis}
@end enumerate


@section Migration Path


@subsection Phase 1: Beads for New Work
@itemize @bullet
@item
Install beads CLI
@item
Add @code{bd} commands alongside existing SQLite
@item
New answers go to both stores
@item
Validate beads captures everything needed
@end itemize


@subsection Phase 2: Quint for Decisions
@itemize @bullet
@item
Install quint MCP server
@item
Add @code{/q*} commands to Claude workflow
@item
Track decisions on complex questions only
@item
Build decision query patterns
@end itemize


@subsection Phase 3: Synthesis Commands
@itemize @bullet
@item
Implement @code{form-copilot synthesize} subcommand
@item
Pattern detection first (most immediately useful)
@item
Cross-reference and decay follow
@end itemize


@subsection Phase 4: SQLite Removal
@itemize @bullet
@item
Migrate historical answers to beads
@item
Remove SQLite code paths
@item
Update documentation
@end itemize


@section Open Questions

@enumerate
@item
@strong{Beads hierarchy depth} - Should sections be beads or just labels?
@item
@strong{Quint granularity} - Decision trail per question or per session?
@item
@strong{Synthesis storage} - Separate beads repo or same as answers?
@item
@strong{Offline operation} - Both tools work offline; any edge cases?
@end enumerate


@section Success Criteria

@itemize @bullet
@item
[ ] New answers stored in beads, queryable via @code{bd}
@item
[ ] At least one decision trail captured in quint
@item
[ ] @code{synthesize patterns} returns meaningful output
@item
[ ] No regression in existing menu workflow
@item
[ ] SQLite fully removed (Phase 4)
@end itemize


